====================================================================================
Die Prep Guidelines
====================================================================================

Customer's design shall contain and fit within a seal ring. The seal ring's bounding
box is 3.6mm x 5.2mm and shall be placed at (0,0) in the top-level of the layout
hierarchy, with an integrated die ID placed at (180,52).

Cadence will issue an 8-character die ID and supply the necessary physical design
collateral to support these requirements. (See below)

The top-level cell in the Customer's design shall be named <designName>_<dieID>,
where <designName> is at the Customer's discretion, and <dieID> is issued by
Cadence (ex: cadencechip_2506ABCD). The OASIS design file shall be named in
accordance with the previously stated requirements and compressed using
Gzip (ex: cadencechip_2506ABCD.oas.gz).

